idCitation.resTitle: Queensland Parks and Wildlife Service fire history

citRespParty.rpIndName: DES, QPWS&P, PS, TS, MAN Spatial Services

dataExt.exDesc: This dataset includes historical burns and other treatments captured from historical record from 1930 onwards. Historical records are incomplete. The first fire management and planning system was introduced in 1999 and a more complete set of fires are repesented in the dataset since then.

dataIdInfo.idPurp: This dataset provides the extent, ignition date and the date the fire was declare out, for fires and mechanical treatments that have started on Queensland Parks and Wildlife Service (QPWS) managed land or State Land Management managed land (State Land) or have spread from neighbouring properties onto this land.
dataIdInfo.idAbs: This dataset shows the history of fires and other treatments (e.g. mechanical treatments such as mowing, slashing and vegetation clearing) and active fires and treatments. It includes both planned burns and wildfires. The fire history includes fires that date back to the 1930s, however fires that occured before the first fire planning and management system was developed in 1999-2000, were entered in an ad-hoc fashion from historical records and are therefore incomplete.
dataIdInfo.idCredit: © State of Queensland (Department of Environment and Science), 2019
dataIdInfo.suppInfo: Areas that have been burnt or treated mechanically are captured in the fire planning and management system (FLAME). Shapes are constructed from features in various reference layers including regional ecosystems and fire regime groups, tracks used as fire breaks, NAFI fire scars, property boundaries, aerial imagery and other layers. Other systems are used to process satelilite and aerial imagery to generate fire scar boundaries. Small fire scars and treatments are captured with GPS units in the field. While active fires and other treatments are included in the dataset, there may be a delay of up to a month, before fires and treatments are entered into FLAME, due to operational priorities.

resMaint.maintNote: The dataset is automatically updated from daily extracts from fire situation reports and burnt areas from the fire management and planning system (FLAME).

enttyp.enttypd: An area burnt or mechanically treated on or near Queensalnd Parks and WIldlife managed land.

attrdomv.udom: Sequential unique whole numbers that are automatically generated.

attr.attrdef: Unique label for the fire/treatment. Composed of reserve name, year and number.

attrdomv.udom: Generated by FLAME when creating a new planned burn for wildfire.

attr.attrdef: Fire/treatment type. Planned burn or wildfire.
Status of the burn. Going, safe or out.
The date the fire/treatment was completed

attrdomv.udom: The date entered into FLAME for the last "Out" situation report.

attr.attrdef: The year the fire/treatment was completed. Calculated from out date or ignition date.

attrdomv.udom: Calculated from out date or ignition date.

attr.attrdef: The month the fire/treatment was completed. Calculated from the out date or ignition date.

attrdomv.udom: Calculated from out date or ignition date

attr.attrdef: The percentage of the burn are that burnt. Different burn conditions can result in patchy burns.
Area of burn in hectares. Calculate from the geometry.
Area of feature in internal units squared.

attrdomv.udom: Positive real numbers that are automatically generated.

report.measDesc: This dataset is updated from situation reports and fire reports entered into the fire management system (FLAME). While situation reports should be entered while the treatment is being carried out, due to operation priorities the final fire report may not appear in the system for up to a month after the treatement was completed or the wild fire was put out.

ConResult.conExpl: Historical records prior to 1999 were limited to ranger knowlege and historical paper records. As such these records are incomplete. It is estimated that approximately 16% of fires and other treatments that occured on QPWS managed lands between 1999 and 2015 are not represented in this dataset.

report.measDesc: The attribute data is of varying consistence. Many records entered into the fire management system between 1999 and 2013 only including an ignition date. Where an "out" date has not be captured, the out year and month were calculated from the ignition date using a one week burn period. For multi-stage burns conducted over several years, the ignition date is the ignition date of the first burn and the out date is the out date of the last burn. Due to a lack of validation tools in the fire management system some igniton and fire out dates are inconsistent.

The shapes of treatment and wildfire extents have varying positional accuracy. Due to a limited ability to survey large or inaccessable areas the extents of historical burnt areas areas in many cases is a best guess. Where back burning or planned burns are ignited along a fire line the spatial represetation of that boundary of the burnt area shares the accuracy of the fire line dataset.

Areas are calcualted from the geometry of the records. Percentage burnt is an estimate of the area burnt provided by the ranger and is not records until the fire report is complete. Percentage burnt is not a manadatory field

dataLineage.statement: This dataset is compiled from historical records entered into the ParkInfo fire management system between 1999 and December 2015 and includes active and historical fires entered into the FLAME fire management system after December 2015.
